    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear mandate: exploit the soft matchups against pitchers like Feltner and M\u00e1rquez to drive up our core counting stats. **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.76) stand as our elite-tier plays, both benefiting from ideal order placement and high-ceiling matchups. **Tucker** is the primary anchor, utilizing a 14% park factor boost at Coors-adjacent levels of hitter-friendly environments and a favorable platoon advantage against Feltner. **Henderson**, meanwhile, maximizes his 81.76 score by combining his leadoff duties with a +14% platoon edge, effectively offsetting the minor efficiency dip caused by the opponent's ability to hold runners. **Andy Pages** also projects for a high-efficiency outing (74.43), as his matchup against Feltner combined with a slow pitcher delivery window provides a prime opportunity to chase those scarce stolen bases we prioritize.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Nasim Nunez** (57.95), who fell just shy of the active roster despite his speed profile. While **Nunez** remains a high-upside asset, his projected efficiency against Houser was cannibalized by a lower batting order position and a defensive matchup against an elite catcher with a 1.86s pop time. Consequently, we opted for the higher base-power reliability of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Josh Lowe** (71.68) to fill those slots. We are monitoring the status of **Jackson Merrill** (56.24); his score assumes a #3 spot in the order, but if the final lineup configuration shifts him down, we will need to re-evaluate his exposure against Kikuchi\u2019s challenging pitch mix. Aside from the volatility inherent in **Merrill**\u2019s pending status, the lineup is optimized to maximize plate appearances in the most favorable environments available.",
